The Category Grid Prompt
"A clean, professional e-commerce website section featuring a four-column image grid for football apparel. Above the grid is a wide header with a bold sans-serif title 'Football Jerseys' on the left and a short paragraph of descriptive marketing text on the right. The four grid images include: 1. A top-down 'flat lay' of folded colorful club jerseys (Liverpool, AC Milan, Real Madrid). 2. Two light blue training tracksuits hanging on a minimalist wooden wall rack. 3. Vintage 'Retro' AC Milan jerseys hanging on a metal clothing rack. 4. A male model in a studio setting wearing a cream-colored lifestyle hoodie. Each image has a bold white overlay title at the bottom: 'Jerseys', 'Tracksuits', 'Retro', and 'Hoodies'. Minimalist white background, high-contrast studio lighting, sleek sportswear aesthetic."

Design Elements Breakdown
If you are trying to replicate the user experience (UX) of this image, here are the key features:

Split Header: The "F-pattern" layout uses the left side for the primary heading (SEO and branding) and the right side for secondary details, keeping the top of the page airy.

Visual Variety: Note how the four images aren't all the same style. It mixes product-only shots (flat lays/hangers) with lifestyle photography (the model). This prevents the grid from looking repetitive.

Typography Hierarchy: * Main Title: Large, dark gray/black, high weight.

Body Text: Small, readable, justified to the right.

Category Labels: Large, white, centered at the bottom of each image to act as clear navigational "buttons."

Color Story: The grid uses a consistent "clean" background (whites and light grays) to let the vibrant colors of the team kits provide the visual pop.